area_name: Doo Doo Doo Doo Doo Doo Boulder

content.description:
Climb face between pine growing in middle of boulder and pine at top of boulder.

Note: avoid the flakes on left side, they look ready to snap off.

Descent: Crab-walk down the backside ramp (careful, it's more slippery than it looks).

Name inspired by the Baby Shark Dance Remix.
content.location: On the "doo doo doo doo doo doo" boulder, 30 yards east of the main area, south side of trail.

content.description:
Rock onto blob o' rock at base of boulder, follow thin rail up left, then top out over the V-groove using the "thank god" blow-hole pocket (if you can find it).

May add a grade of difficulty if wing-span is under 6'.

Descent: Crab-walk down the backside ramp (careful, it's more slippery than it looks).

Name inspired by the Baby Shark Dance Remix.
content.location: On the "doo doo doo doo doo doo" boulder, 35 yards east of the main area, south side of trail.

content.description:
Climb the edge-filled face right of the small pine growing in the middle of the boulder. Lots of variations possible.

Descent: Crab-walk down the backside ramp (careful, it's more slippery than it looks).

Name inspired by the Baby Shark Dance Remix.
